node.text:
Refreshed my rhubarb shortcake recipe for you and it now has two gravel smoothing elements in it 😂 this is what we call shortcake in Nz - one dough that forms the base and topping. It’s super good with rhubarb but also amazing with stone fruit (plum is 🙌🏻), cranberries or berries. The recipe is linked in my bio! It originally had two pieces of pastry that got rolled out but I sent the recipe to @ohyeahnahbro and she worked some pastry magic on it and made it way easier so I had to also do that 😂💕 enjoy! ❤️
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
It’s already Thursday here and I’m not in the US any more but can’t resist jumping on this chocolate chip cookie bandwagon. Nutella malted milk won the most recent round of recipe hunger games but I have a few other recipes to go out before it, so I’ll send it out to my mailing list tomorrow! You can sign up via my bio (above the pics there’s a link) or I’ll pop a swipe in my stories. All the chocolate chip recipes on my site are linked in my bio too under this image - just out of interest if you’ve made one, which is your fave?! (Shameless request too that if you make blogger’s recipes leaving a review is SO HELPFUL for all the good SEO google vibes!) ok that’s all happy chocolate chip internet useless holiday day!
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Our stuff isn’t set to arrive until early sept and so I probably won’t start “working” again until late sept while we settle into the house (v thankful for an epic recipe backlog I have to tide us all over for now) but I had to leave all my appliances behind as I didn’t want to have to rewire the kitchen for a different frequency and voltage. It was very very fun playing appliance mama claus to our friends before we left though 💕 anyway I just ordered myself a new mixer and I think the first thing I will make when it arrives is a big batch of these super squishy dinner rolls. They are so fun to make, are drowned in garlic butter, and the recipe doubles perfectly if you need 24. Recipe linked in my bio!
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Hiiiii minute long reels! This strawberry rhubarb crumble pie is on my website right now. There’s a strawberry rhubarb filling, and a malted milk brown butter crumble (!!) that I want to put on everything. Recipe link is in my bio! I love this one and I hope you do too. No finished video by the looks (this was made about a week before we moved because I have approximately zero chill) but there’s finished pics on the blog 🥰 song is @laurenspencersmith 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Hello hi and welcome to the next round of the hunger games aka what goes on my website next out of the backlog I have ready for you! Today’s category is small batch chocolate chip cookies and the contenders are malted milk Nutella, brown butter macadamia milk chocolate, and brown butter thin and crispy. Who would you like to see first? Let me know in the comments! Ps if you’d like to get an email every time a new recipe goes up, you can sign up via the link in my bio. And also as always just a wee thanks for being here in my corner of the internet. I never ever imagined that I would get to do this as my job (it’s my dream job that I wasn’t aware was my dream job) and that I could move across the world and be able to still do it just blows me away every day. I am so incredible grateful you’re all here 😍 seeing my recipes be recreated in your homes is just the best feeling ever ever and will always outweigh any marilyn that comes my way 😂. Ok that’s enough sloppiness, please vote on your cookie preference. 💕💕💕💕
.
.
.
.

node.text: Super twisty cinnamon sugar babka is live on @kana.goods website today! There’s a soft and fluffy dough, a cinnamon cardamom filing, and the whole thing is rolled in cinnamon sugar to finish. I used @Kana.goods quarter sheet pan pre-cut parchment paper which is a work horse in my kitchen - I love how easy it is to line a loaf pan with it, and the overhang makes removing the loaf after baking just too easy. Link for the recipe is in my bio, and you can use the code CLOUDYKITCHEN10 for 10% off on the Kana website. Enjoy! #sponsored #goodsmadebetter

node.text:
Happy Wednesday / Thursday / doughnut day / whatever day it is where you are 💕 these chocolate pudding doughnuts come from a super fun collab @mikebakesnyc and I did last year where we turned thanksgiving flavours into doughnuts! You can see all the other ones on my blog linked in my profile 💕 we just used the one brioche base which we changed up flavour wise. It’s the same dough I use for babka and cinnamon rolls and pull-apart bread - we love a versatile base recipe 🥰
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
I had lots of questions about if you can make my small batch brioche in the mixer - yes, you absolutely can. The reason I developed it by hand though is that I know not everyone has one and I wanted something that could be nice and versatile! Plus sometimes it’s just fun to make stuff by hand, just because. These buns can be made with basically any fruit (or none and just have custard buns!) so are also super versatile. Recipe is in my bio and step by step is in my highlights! I have two more rhubarb recipes to come - can you still get it where you are? One is a re-work of an old recipe that makes it waaaay easier and the other is a strawberry rhubarb pie with a malted milk streusel that is 🔥
.
.
.
.
.
